 chop <b>3 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add mince, chilli flakes, cumin, coriander, paprika, salt, pepper and dried mint and mix <b>10 sec\/\/speed 3<b>, until well combined. Divide into 4 portions (approx. 130 g each), then roll into four sausages (approx. 12 cm in length). Set aside."},{"content":"On a silicone bread mat or clean work surface, roll reserved dough into a large rectangle (30 x 34 cm) and cut into 4 rectangles. Place 1 reserved sausage onto each rectangle horizontally along long edge. Brush all edges with water and roll up lightly to enclose sausages. Press sides of the pastry together to form a sealed roll. Brush rolls with oil."},{"content":"Place a large frying pan over medium-high heat and fry rolls, turning regularly, until browned on all sides (approx. 5 minutes). Turn heat down to low and cook, turning frequently, until cooked through (approx. for a further 10 minutes - see Tips)."},{"content":"Serve lamb rolls with reserved Yoghurt dressing and lemon wedges (see Tips)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can shallow fry Greek rolls in a frying pan over medium heat for a crispy, brown finish, if desired. Cooking times may vary.","We served our lamb rolls with a Greek salad on the side.","To mince your own meat, please refer to the guide in the front of <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>. Please note that it may increase the total time of the recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","4 portions"]}